text: manual describes estimate chronological gestational DNA methylation (DNAm) age well biological age using different methylation clocks. package includes following estimators:

title: Chronological and gestational DNAm age estimation using different methylation-based clocks
text: AgeAcDiff (DNAmAge acceleration difference): Difference DNAmAge chronological age. IEAA Residuals obtained regressing DNAmAge chronological age adjusted cell counts. EEAA Residuals obtained regressing DNAmAge chronological age. measure also known DNAmAge acceleration residual first Horvath’s paper. AMAR (Apparent Methylomic Aging Rate): Measure proposed Hannum et al. (2013) computed ratio DNAm age chronological age. BNN: uses Horvath’s CpGs train Bayesian Neural Network (BNN) predict DNAm age described Alfonso Gonzalez (2020). Horvath’s skin+blood clock (skinHorvath): Epigenetic clock skin blood cells. uses 391 CpGs described Horvath et al. (2018). trained using 450K EPIC arrays skin blood sampels. PedBE clock: Epigenetic clock buccal epithelial swabs. ’s intended purpose buccal samples individuals aged 0-20 years old. uses 84 CpGs described McEwen et al. (2019). authors gathered 1,721 genome-wide DNAm profiles 11 different cohorts individuals aged 0 20 years old. Wu’s clock: uses 111 CpGs described Wu et al. (2019). designed predict age children. trained using 27K 450K. BLUP clock: uses 319607 CpGs described Zhang et al. (2019). trained using 450K EPIC arrays blood (13402 samples) saliva (259 samples). Age predictors based training sets various sample sizes using Best Linear Unbiased Prediction (BLUP) EN clock: uses 514 CpGs described Zhang et al. (2019). trained using 450K EPIC arrays blood (13402 samples) saliva (259 samples). Age predictors based training sets various sample sizes using Elastic Net (EN) PMA 450K Post-menstrual age (PMA), uses 409 CpGs trained using 450K arrays. PMA EPIC Post-menstrual age (PMA), uses 522 CpGs trained using EPIC arrays. PNA 450K Postnatal age (PNA) equivalent chronological age time elapsed birth, uses 303 CpGs trained using 450K arrays. PNA EPIC Postnatal age (PNA) equivalent chronological age time elapsed birth, uses 509 CpGs trained using EPIC arrays.

title: Chronological and gestational DNAm age estimation using different methylation-based clocks
text: Knight’s clock: uses 148 CpGs described Knight et al. (2016). trained using 27K 450K arrays cord blood samples. Bohlin’s clock: uses 96 CpGs described Bohlin et al. (2016). trained using 450K array cord blood samples. Mayne’s clock: uses 62 CpGs described Mayne et al. (2017). trained using 27K 450K. EPIC clock: EPIC-based predictor gestational age. uses 176 CpGs described Haftorn et al. (2021). trained using EPIC arrays cord blood samples. RPC clock: Robust placental clock (RPC). uses 558 CpG sites. CPC clock: Control placental clock (CPC). usses 546 CpG sites. Refined RPC clock: Useful uncomplicated term pregnancies (e.g. gestational age >36 weeks). uses 396 CpG sites. biological DNAm clocks implemented package : Levine’s clock (also know PhenoAge): uses 513 CpGs described Levine et al. (2018). trained using 27K, 450K EPIC arrays blood samples. Telomere Length’s clock (TL): uses 140 CpGs described Lu et al. (2019) trained using 450K EPIC arrays blood samples. main aim package facilitate interconnection R Bioconductor’s infrastructure , hence, avoiding submitting data online calculators. Additionally, methylclock also provides unified way computing DNAm age help downstream analyses.

title: Chronological and gestational DNAm age estimation using different methylation-based clocks
text: EEAA method requires estimate cell counts. use package meffil (Min et al. (2018)) provides functions estimate cell counts using predefined datasets. performed setting cell.count=TRUE (default value). reference panel passed argument cell.count.reference. far, following options available: “blood gse35069 complete”: methylation profiles Reinius et al. (2012) purified blood cell types. includes CD4T, CD8T, Mono, Bcell, NK, Neu Eos. “blood gse35069”: methylation profiles Reinius et al. (2012) purified blood cell types. includes CD4T, CD8T, Mono, Bcell, NK Gran. “blood gse35069 chen”: methylation profiles Chen et al. (2017) blood cell types. includes CD4T, CD8T, Mono, Bcell, NK, Neu Eos. “andrews bakulski cord blood”. Cord blood reference Bakulski et al. (2016). includes Bcell, CD4T, CD8T, Gran, Mono, NK nRBC. “cord blood gse68456” Cord blood methylation profiles Goede et al. (2015). includes CD4T, CD8T, Mono, Bcell, NK, Neu, Eos RBC. “gervin lyle cord blood” Cord blood reference generated Kristina Gervin Robert Lyle, available miffil package. includes CD14, Bcell, CD4T, CD8T, NK, Gran. “saliva gse48472”: Reference generated multi-tissue pannel Slieker et al. (2013). includes Buccal, CD4T, CD8T, Mono, Bcell, NK, Gran. “guintivano dlpfc”: Reference generated Guintivano, Aryee, Kaminsky (2013). includes dorsolateral prefrontal cortex, NeuN_neg NeuN_pos. “combined cord blood”: References generated based samples assayed Bakulski et al, Gervin et al., de Goede et al., Lin et al. includes umbilical cord blood, Bcell, CD4T, CD8T, Gran, Mono, NK nRBC “placenta”: References Yuan et al. (2021), Yuan (2022). includes placental cells third trimester Trophoblasts, Stromal, Hofbauer, Endothelial, nRBC, Syncytiotrophoblast.

title: Chronological and gestational DNAm age estimation using different methylation-based clocks
text: methylclock package allows estimate chronological gestational DNA methylation (DNAm) age well biological age using different methylation clocks. package includes following estimators:

title: Chronological and gestational DNAm age estimation using different methylation-based clocks
text: AgeAcDiff (DNAmAge acceleration difference): Difference DNAmAge chronological age. IEAA Residuals obtained regressing DNAmAge chronological age adjusted cell counts. EEAA Residuals obtained regressing DNAmAge chronological age. measure also known DNAmAge acceleration residual first Horvath’s paper. AMAR (Apparent Methylomic Aging Rate): Measure proposed @hannum2013genome computed ratio DNAm age chronological age. BNN: uses Horvath’s CpGs train Bayesian Neural Network (BNN) predict DNAm age described @alfonso2018. Horvath’s skin+blood clock (skinHorvath): Epigenetic clock skin blood cells. uses 391 CpGs described @horvath2018epigenetic. trained using 450K EPIC arrays skin blood sampels. PedBE clock: Epigenetic clock buccal epithelial swabs. ’s intended purpose buccal samples individuals aged 0-20 years old. uses 84 CpGs described @mcewen2019pedbe. authors gathered 1,721 genome-wide DNAm profiles 11 different cohorts individuals aged 0 20 years old. Wu’s clock: uses 111 CpGs described @wu2019dna. designed predict age children. trained using 27K 450K. Best Linear Unbiased Prediction (BLUP) clock: uses 319607 CpGs described @zhang2019improved. trained using 450K EPIC arrays blood (13402 samples) saliva (259 samples). Age predictors based training sets various sample sizes using Best Linear Unbiased Prediction (BLUP) Elastic Net (EN) clock: uses 514 CpGs described @zhang2019improved. trained using 450K EPIC arrays blood (13402 samples) saliva (259 samples). Age predictors based training sets various sample sizes using Elastic Net (EN) PMA 450K Post-menstrual age (PMA), uses 409 CpGs trained using 450K arrays. PMA EPIC Post-menstrual age (PMA), uses 522 CpGs trained using EPIC arrays. PNA 450K Postnatal age (PNA) equivalent chronological age time elapsed birth, uses 303 CpGs trained using 450K arrays. PNA EPIC Postnatal age (PNA) equivalent chronological age time elapsed birth, uses 509 CpGs trained using EPIC arrays.

title: Chronological and gestational DNAm age estimation using different methylation-based clocks
text: Knight’s clock: uses 148 CpGs described @knight2016epigenetic. trained using 27K 450K arrays cord blood samples. Bohlin’s clock: uses 96 CpGs described @bohlin2016prediction. trained using 450K array cord blood samples. Mayne’s clock: uses 62 CpGs described @mayne2017accelerated. trained using 27K 450K. EPIC clock: EPIC-based predictor gestational age. uses 176 CpGs described @haftorn2021epic. trained using EPIC arrays cord blood samples. RPC clock: Robust placental clock (RPC). uses 558 CpG sites. CPC clock: Control placental clock (CPC). usses 546 CpG sites. Refined RPC clock: Useful uncomplicated term pregnancies (e.g. gestational age >36 weeks). uses 396 CpG sites. biological DNAm clocks implemented package : Levine’s clock (also know PhenoAge): uses 513 CpGs described @levine2018epigenetic. trained using 27K, 450K EPIC arrays blood samples. Telomere Length’s clock (TL): uses 140 CpGs described @lu2019dna trained using 450K EPIC arrays blood samples. 1 EPIC clock years
